Preprocessing data¶

In [5]:
# function to extract year from date columns
extract_year <- function(s) {
  match <- regmatches(s, regexpr("\\b\\d{4}\\b", s))
  if (length(match) == 0) return(NA)
  return(match)
}

nobel <- nobel_raw %>% 
  rename(prize_year = year,
         country = bornCountry) %>% 
  mutate(#prize_year = as.numeric(year),
         birth_year = as.numeric(extract_year(born)),
         age = case_when( gender != "org" ~ prize_year - birth_year,
                          TRUE ~ NA_real_),
         category = str_to_sentence(category)
         )

Nobel Laureates by Decade and Prize Category¶

This plot shows the number of Nobel laureates awarded each decade, separated by prize category.

Chemistry, medicine, and physics have consistently high numbers, with peaks around the 2000s.

Economics starts appearing only from the late 20th century, reflecting the prize’s later establishment.

Literature shows relatively stable laureate counts over time.

Peace prize laureates fluctuate more, with notable dips during major global conflicts.

In [13]:
nobel %>% 
  group_by(decade = 10 * (prize_year %/% 10), category) %>% 
  count() %>% 
  ggplot(aes(decade, n, fill = category)) +
  geom_col() +
  scale_fill_colorblind() +
  facet_wrap(~category) +  
  labs(
    x = "Decades",
    y = "Number of laureates",
    title = "Nobel Laureates by Decade and Category",
    subtitle = "Number of laureates awarded in each decade, separated by prize category",
    fill = "Prize category"
  )
In [14]:
nobel %>% 
  group_by(decade = 10 * (prize_year %/% 10), category) %>% 
  mutate(winners = n(),
         winners_per_year = winners / n_distinct(prize_year)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(decade, winners_per_year, color = category)) +
  geom_line(linewidth = 0.85) +
  expand_limits(y = 0) +
  labs(
    x = "Decade",
    y = "Average laureates per year",
    color = "Category",
    title = "Average Annual Number of Nobel Laureates per Decade",
    subtitle = "Average number of laureates per year in each decade, shown by prize category"
  )

nobel %>%
  mutate(Laureate_Type = ifelse(gender %in% c("female", "male"), "Individual", "Organization")) %>%
  group_by(fullName) %>%
  arrange(prize_year) %>% 
  summarise(
    laureate_type = first(Laureate_Type),
    categories    = paste(unique(category), collapse = " & "),
    years = paste(unique(prize_year), collapse = " & "),
    times_won     = n(),
    .groups = "drop"
  ) %>%
  arrange(desc(times_won)) %>%
  filter(times_won > 1)

nobel %>% 
  filter(!is.na(age)) %>% 
  group_by(decade = 10 * (prize_year %/% 10), category) %>% 
  summarize(avg_age = mean(age)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(decade, avg_age, color = category)) +
  geom_line(linewidth = 0.85)

`summarise()` has grouped output by 'decade'. You can override using the
`.groups` argument.
